                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d414">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.74/198: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schurman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-12-02T18:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 2, 1921—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 2—10:55 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>428. British Minister handed note two days ago to the Minister for Foreign
                    Affairs protesting against Federal wireless contract [<hi rend="italic"
                        >and?</hi>] Government’s breach of faith. Yen renewed to me today hope
                    formerly expressed that American Government could find solution.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Schurman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
